SIMPLE: stratification
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stratification
<hw>Strat`i*fi*ca"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>stratification</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or process of
laying in strata, or the state of being laid in the form of strata, or
layers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The deposition of material in
successive layers in the growth of a cell wall, thus giving rise to a
stratified appearance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stratified</ent>⟦br⟧
